Yu Qian (1398-1457), styled Tingyi, styled Jie 'an, Han nationality, was born in Qiantang County, Hangzhou City, Zhejiang Province (now Shangcheng District, Hangzhou City, Zhejiang Province). He was a famous minister and national hero of Ming Dynasty. In the 19th year of Yongle (1421), Yu Qian ascended the rank of Jinshi. In the first year of Xuande (1426), he followed Emperor Xuanzong of Ming Dynasty to put down the chaos of King Zhu Gaoxu, and was appreciated by Emperor Xuanzong because of his stern words against Zhu Gaoxu, and was promoted to patrol Jiangxi, singing songs full of road. Xuande five years (1430), to the military department right squire governor of Henan, Shanxi and other places. Emperor Yingzong of the Ming Dynasty was falsely accused and sent to prison because he did not give gifts to the powerful minister Wang Zhen when he entered the capital for an audience, but he was reinstated due to the efforts of the people, officials and even the king of the two provinces. After the change of civil engineering, the British emperor was captured after the defeat of the army, he was forced to row south of the discussion, firm please hold, promoted to the ministry of war. Emperor of Ming Dynasty took the throne, ordered troops to prepare, deployed key points, personally supervised the battle, led 220,000 divisions, and marched outside the nine gates of Beijing to resist the Wara army. The Wara Taiji also forced Yingzong to make peace. He put the state first and the king first and refused to allow it. He also had no excuse, so he was forced to release Emperor Yingzong. After the peace negotiations, Yu Qian still actively prepared for war, selected the elite of the Jing army to drill in ten regiments, and sent troops out of the customs to garrison, so that the border could be peaceful. At that time, the affairs of the court were complicated, and Yu Qian's independent dispatch was in line with the opportune situation. His orders were clear and administrative. He worried about the country forgot his body, did not speak merit, scrimping, living only to shelter the wind and rain. But because of his straightforwardness, he incurred the hatred of all. In the first year of Tianshun (1457), Emperor Yingzong was restored, and the general Shi Heng falsely accused Yu Qian of seeking to appoint the son of King Xiang, resulting in his unjust death. In the reign of Emperor Xianzong of Ming Dynasty, Yu Qian was honored with a sacrificial title. In the second year of Hongzhi (1489), he was posthumously awarded the posthumous title of Su Min. During the reign of Emperor Shenzong, he changed his posthumous title to Zhongsu. There is Yu Zhongsu collection handed down. The History of the Ming Dynasty praised him as loyal and courageous, winning glory with the sun and the moon.
